Rooms.RoomDescription: `hLarge, marble pillars line both sides of this massive hall. Thoughit  is quite large, corners  of it can be intimate.  At one end ofthis rectangular room, a large marble fireplace stands with an oldoaken  mantle  atop it. Several  comfortable,  high-backed leatherchairs are  scattered  around the fireplace.  The other end of themassive chamber houses a large bar.  A gigantic  golden harp restson top of a three-tiered pedestal  in the  center of the room. Nowand then, beautiful music can be heard by the harp which magicallyplays itself.  Various  plants and small trees in pots can be seenhere  and there next to couches,  chairs  and footstools that havebeen strategically placed around the room. The most dramatic thingabout the room, however, is the windows. Tall picture windows linethree sides of this cavernous chamber with the exception being thewall with the fireplace and the exit.  Almost all of Exodus can beseen far below, through the crystal-clear windows. You  freeze andshudder with the majesty of all that you see.

Almost all of Exodus can be seen far below, through thecrystal-clear windows.  You shudder with the majesty of all that you see.

`gThe translucent dome is a glory to behold.  It shimmers in thesunlight, casting shadows upon it's glossy floor as birds fly overhead.  Thevery air inside glitters with a magical aura, intangible and full ofmystery.  The glass of the floor echoes footsteps throughout the great hallas animals of all forms wander freely.

`c A breath of fresh air takes over your lungs as you enter this smallbut lush field.  The green grass stands out against the sky making the restof the world seem dull and colorless.  Flowers emerge from the ground inevery direction filling the air with the sweet smell of nature.  Tinydroplets form on blades of grass creating a sparkling affect that shimmersin the sunlight.  Trees form a straight line on either side of the fieldleading up to a crystal dome ahead in the distance.
